    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; DT, 9 and 10 Engine Service Manual - Cylinder Head and Valve Train -
        Recondition - Replace Valve Guides
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="replace" graphiccount="2">
        <title>Replace Valve Guides</title>
        <figure id="f3350013373" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figh08/h08036.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Press out valve guide insert</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Press ram</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Valve Guide Remover</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Replace Valve guides if damaged or out of specifications.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, do not use a hammer or other improper tool to remove or install valve
                    guides.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Secure cylinder head on a press table with the gasket surface down.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Insert
                <hotlnk document="eges3351_341.xml" xrefid="t335001303">Valve Guide Remover</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="t335001303"/>
                in the valve guide from the top side of the cylinder head.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Align Valve Guide Remover and valve guide to be replaced with center of press ram and press
                out valve guide insert.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Chilling valve guide inserts may help installation.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f3350013374" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figk08/k08017.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Press in valve guide insert</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Press ram</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Valve Guide Installer</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Valve guide insert</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lubricate each new valve guide insert with clean engine oil.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Center valve guide insert and
                <hotlnk document="eges3351_341.xml" xrefid="t335001303">Valve Guide Installer</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="t335001303"/>
                under press ram and install valve guide insert until installer bottoms out against cylinder head.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Do not ream inside diameter of valve guide after installation. Service valve guides are finish
                    reamed.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">After installing valve guide insert, debur valve guide with
                <hotlnk document="eges3351_341.xml" xrefid="t335001303">Valve Guide Deburring Tool</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="t335001303"/>.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
